numericStringToBigInteger

public static BigInteger numericStringToBigInteger(String numeric)
Converts a numeric string to a BigInteger. This function first converts to a BigDecimal to make sure the base number being used is accurate. By default, this method uses the ROUND_HALF_UP rounding method from BigDecimal. If the string cannot be converted, this method returns null

Parameters:
numeric - A numeric string (with or without decimals).
Returns:
BigInteger representation of the string or null.
See Also:
BigDecimal

numericStringToBigInteger

public static BigInteger numericStringToBigInteger(String numeric,
                                                   boolean round)
Converts a numeric string to a BigInteger. This function first converts to a BigDecimal to make sure the base number being used is accurate. If round is set to true this method uses the ROUND_HALF_UP rounding method from BigDecimal. Otherwise the decimal part is dropped. If the string cannot be converted, this method returns null

Parameters:
numeric - A numeric string (with or without decimals).
round - Use BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP method.
Returns:
BigInteger representation of the string or null
See Also:
BigDecimal
